00:22:22.640 --> 00:22:26.930
The Ig Nobel Prize for
Physics was awarded to a team

00:22:26.930 --> 00:22:30.030
from Italy, Russia, and
several other countries.

00:22:30.030 --> 00:22:31.670
The work was mostly
done in Italy.

00:22:32.820 --> 00:22:35.890
They discovered that
some people would

00:22:35.890 --> 00:22:42.810
be physically capable of running
across the surface of a pond

00:22:42.810 --> 00:22:47.650
if those people and that
pond were on the moon.

00:22:51.030 --> 00:22:53.130
Here's their paper about
it called "Humans Running

00:22:53.130 --> 00:22:56.225
in Place on Water at
Simulated Reduced Gravity."

00:22:56.225 --> 00:22:59.410
It was published in "PLOS
ONE," a very good journal.

00:22:59.410 --> 00:23:01.510
Many of the things that
have won Ig Nobel Prizes

00:23:01.510 --> 00:23:03.009
have been published
in top journals.

00:23:03.860 --> 00:23:05.790
Many have been published
in bottom journals

00:23:05.790 --> 00:23:08.540
and many not published at all.

00:23:08.540 --> 00:23:10.020
By the way, it's
not just science.

00:23:10.020 --> 00:23:15.000
We can give and do give Ig Nobel
Prizes in pretty much anything.

00:23:15.000 --> 00:23:17.240
Most years we give
out a Peace Prize.

00:23:17.240 --> 00:23:20.650
We a couple times have
given out an Art Prize.

00:23:20.650 --> 00:23:23.030
The first time we gave out
an Ig Nobel Prize in Art,

00:23:23.030 --> 00:23:25.690
it went to a man named
Don Featherstone.

00:23:25.690 --> 00:23:28.180
He's the creator of the
plastic pink flamingo.

00:23:30.499 --> 00:23:32.290
And if you'd come to
the Ig Nobel Ceremony,

00:23:32.290 --> 00:23:33.248
you could have met him.

00:23:34.370 --> 00:23:38.330
This is some of the work done
about-- what they were trying

00:23:38.330 --> 00:23:42.510
to figure out was if
you were to somehow make

00:23:42.510 --> 00:23:45.390
the force of gravity
weaker on earth,

00:23:45.390 --> 00:23:47.400
how much weaker
would it have to be

00:23:47.400 --> 00:23:49.710
before an ordinary
person could walk

00:23:49.710 --> 00:23:51.804
across the surface of water?

00:23:51.804 --> 00:23:53.470
There are some animals
that can do that.

00:23:53.470 --> 00:23:56.390
There are a few lizards
and some insects that

00:23:56.390 --> 00:23:59.960
are able to walk across the
surface of water, but not many.

00:23:59.960 --> 00:24:03.590
And as it worked out in
the calculations and then

00:24:03.590 --> 00:24:05.970
when they did some
experiments, it

00:24:05.970 --> 00:24:08.240
turned out that the
surface of the moon

00:24:08.240 --> 00:24:10.150
just happens to be
right at the level

00:24:10.150 --> 00:24:14.230
where if there were water there,
and you can walk and breathe

00:24:14.230 --> 00:24:17.340
and all, you could walk
across that surface.

