00:35:00.400 --> 00:35:04.170
I want to finish with one
other little piece of video

00:35:04.170 --> 00:35:06.487
from the ceremony
a couple weeks ago.

00:35:06.487 --> 00:35:08.070
And I'll introduce
it because it, too,

00:35:08.070 --> 00:35:09.960
has a connection to you.

00:35:09.960 --> 00:35:13.180
You may recognize this
man, Ray Kurzweil.

00:35:14.945 --> 00:35:17.130
Ray's title is,
I think, Director

00:35:17.130 --> 00:35:20.070
of Engineering,
something like that?

00:35:20.070 --> 00:35:22.320
And I worked for Ray
a long time ago back

00:35:22.320 --> 00:35:24.800
at Ray's first company,
Kurzweil Computer Products.

00:35:24.800 --> 00:35:26.170
I was a programmer.

00:35:26.170 --> 00:35:28.210
We were working on optical
character recognition

00:35:28.210 --> 00:35:31.480
things and a machine that
read printed things allowed

00:35:31.480 --> 00:35:35.350
for blind people and
other related stuff.

00:35:35.350 --> 00:35:37.790
But Ray has many
sides, as you may know.

00:35:37.790 --> 00:35:39.650
And one of them has
to do with nutrition.

00:35:39.650 --> 00:35:44.930
Ray, for decades, has been
working on ideas about people

00:35:44.930 --> 00:35:47.990
stopping for the most part
eating what they're eating now

00:35:47.990 --> 00:35:50.860
and having a diet
heavily based on hundreds

00:35:50.860 --> 00:35:53.480
of carefully selected pills.

00:35:53.480 --> 00:35:56.580
And he believes and
has written extensively

00:35:56.580 --> 00:35:58.715
that if you follow
the diet properly,

00:35:58.715 --> 00:36:01.950
you stand a good chance
of living for, perhaps,

00:36:01.950 --> 00:36:03.090
many hundreds of years.

00:36:03.090 --> 00:36:04.330
Maybe even beyond that.

00:36:05.550 --> 00:36:10.950
So every year in our--
well, not so at that point.

00:36:10.950 --> 00:36:14.450
Every year in the Ig Nobel
Ceremony, the heart of it

00:36:14.450 --> 00:36:17.360
is when we introduce
the 10 Ig Nobel Winners.

00:36:17.360 --> 00:36:19.891
But between those announcements,
we do other things.

00:36:19.891 --> 00:36:22.140
And one of the things we do,
the grandest thing we do,

00:36:22.140 --> 00:36:24.010
is every year we
write a little opera

00:36:24.010 --> 00:36:25.900
about something in science.

00:36:25.900 --> 00:36:29.730
We steal music from dead
composers-- Mozart this year--

00:36:29.730 --> 00:36:34.200
and we write a story
and lyrics that

00:36:34.200 --> 00:36:36.730
explain or don't
explain something going

00:36:36.730 --> 00:36:39.150
on now in science
and technology.

00:36:39.150 --> 00:36:43.770
This year, it was about--
I took the idea of Ray,

00:36:43.770 --> 00:36:46.620
or somebody, subsisting
on nothing but pills

00:36:46.620 --> 00:36:48.830
and I twisted that
and extended it

00:36:48.830 --> 00:36:50.960
way off into other directions.

00:36:50.960 --> 00:36:52.150
And I told Ray.

00:36:52.150 --> 00:36:53.590
Invited him to
the ceremony, too.

00:36:53.590 --> 00:36:55.280
Although, he didn't come.

00:36:55.280 --> 00:36:58.790
And what I'm going to
show you is the very end

00:36:58.790 --> 00:37:02.320
of the opera, the last
minute or so of the opera.

00:37:02.320 --> 00:37:04.910
The plot, it's two people.

00:37:04.910 --> 00:37:07.440
It's two wealthy
entrepreneurs who

00:37:07.440 --> 00:37:11.420
follow the idea--
the same one Ray did.

00:37:11.420 --> 00:37:13.130
They stop eating
regular food and they

00:37:13.130 --> 00:37:17.270
decide to get all their
nourishment entirely

00:37:17.270 --> 00:37:19.410
from hundreds and
hundreds of pills.

00:37:19.410 --> 00:37:22.240
And they are very greedy
people in this opera.

00:37:23.250 --> 00:37:24.560
This is very fictional people.

00:37:24.560 --> 00:37:25.920
They are very greedy people.

00:37:25.920 --> 00:37:28.860
And they end up buying all
the farmland in the world

00:37:28.860 --> 00:37:31.610
because they want to ensure
that they're going to survive.

00:37:31.610 --> 00:37:33.040
They do.

00:37:33.040 --> 00:37:34.870
After 600 years,
they're still around,

00:37:34.870 --> 00:37:36.220
but there are no other people.

00:37:36.220 --> 00:37:38.000
It's just them and
their microbes.

00:37:39.140 --> 00:37:40.960
And then something goes wrong.

00:37:40.960 --> 00:37:43.269
All of their pills have been
stored in their basement

00:37:43.269 --> 00:37:44.810
and they've neglected
their plumbing.

00:37:44.810 --> 00:37:47.240
And the plumbing broke and
flooded the basement and all

00:37:47.240 --> 00:37:50.190
of their pills, all their
food supply is gone.

00:37:50.190 --> 00:37:52.830
And they have no skills about
raising food or making pills,

00:37:52.830 --> 00:37:55.500
so they're doomed
and they know it.

00:37:55.500 --> 00:37:58.350
What you're going to see is the
last minute or so of the opera

00:37:58.350 --> 00:38:00.152
when they know they're doomed.

00:38:00.152 --> 00:38:01.860
They're still desperately
trying to think

00:38:01.860 --> 00:38:03.870
of some way to survive.

00:38:03.870 --> 00:38:06.980
And their microbes, who
you will see as a chorus

00:38:06.980 --> 00:38:09.450
all around them, are
not at all unhappy

00:38:09.450 --> 00:38:12.360
because their microbes are
probably going to survive.

00:38:12.360 --> 00:38:16.680
So you're going to see the
two people doomed, panicked,

00:38:16.680 --> 00:38:18.040
and their microbes.

00:38:18.040 --> 00:38:21.660
A chorus of microbes, which
includes four people who

00:38:21.660 --> 00:38:25.690
have Nobel Prizes, who
were kind enough to let us

00:38:25.690 --> 00:38:28.940
stick them in the chorus,
all coming together

00:38:28.940 --> 00:38:31.790
in this glorious
conclusion to the opera.

00:38:31.790 --> 00:38:35.160
The opera is called,
"What's Eating You."

